The paper deals with self-supervised visual representation learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques to improve representation learning, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of the choice of pretext task and dataset on the learned features, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE).
